      Content: Build procedural vertical city generator in Unity
      Kind: unity.citygen.project
      LatestState: INTENT
      Summary: 
      Goal: Coordinate the remaining work needed to turn the current prototype into
        a coherent multi-agent procedural city generator in Unity.
      RoleHint: 
      Priority: 
      Inputs:
      - Docs/Canon/ascending-ward.md
      - Docs/Contracts/generator-architecture.md
      - Docs/Contracts/city-context-schema.md
      - Docs/Contracts/agent-pipeline.md
      - Assets/Scripts/CityGen/
      Outputs:
      - A deterministic semantic graph pipeline
      - A navigable blockout geometry pass
      - A validation pass with concrete repair outputs
      - A working Intentspace coordination loop for the Unity project
      NonGoals:
      - Final art production
      - One-click finished city generation
      - District-specific handcrafted polish
      - Open-ended internet asset crawling
      DoneCondition:
      - The generator produces a coherent vertical city graph from a seed.
      - The blockout is navigable and legible in Scene view.
      - Major systems can be coordinated through Intentspace contracts and artifact
        references.
      ArtifactPaths:
      - Assets/Scripts/CityGen/
      - Assets/CityGen/Exports/
      - Assets/CityGen/Imports/
      - Docs/
      Tags: []
